-- Audi Dominates Podium Positions at Le Mans 24-Hour Race, AFP Reports
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-06-13T14:29:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/audi-dominates-podium-positions-at-le-mans-24-hour-race-afp-reports.html

          
          
             Audi filled the first three places
at motor racing’s Le Mans 24-hour race, Agence France-Presse
reported.  
 The R15 TDI team of France’s Romain Dumas and German duo
Timo Bernhard and Mike Rockenfeller came first, one lap ahead of
France’s Benoit Treluyer, Swiss Marcel Fassler and Andre
Lotterer of Germany, AFP said.  
 Denmark’s Tom Kristensen, Briton Allan McNish and Italy’s
Rinaldo Capello came third, three laps behind the winner.  
          
          


  


        